  "prompt": "Why is the corner of my eye soring?",
  "response": "There are several potential reasons why the corner of your eye might be sore. Some common causes include:\n\n1. **Allergies**: Allergies can cause inflammation and irritation in the eyes, leading to discomfort in the corners.\n\n2. **Infection**: Conditions such as conjunctivitis (pink eye) or blepharitis (inflammation of the eyelids) can cause soreness.\n\n3. **Dry Eyes**: Insufficient moisture in your eyes can lead to irritation and discomfort.\n\n4. **Foreign Object**: Sometimes, a small particle like dust, sand, or an eyelash can get trapped in the eye, causing irritation.\n\n5. **Fatigue or Strain**: Extended screen time or lack of sleep can lead to eye strain, which might result in soreness.\n\n6. **Sinus Issues**: Sinusitis or other sinus problems can cause referred pain in the eye area.\n\n7. **Injury**: A recent trauma or scratch to the eye can lead to soreness.\n\nIf the soreness persists, worsens, or is accompanied by other symptoms like swelling, redness, or vision changes, it's best to consult a healthcare professional or an eye care specialist for a proper diagnosis and treatment.",
